wiki.text:
'Tikhonov' (; masculine), sometimes spelled as 'Tychonoff', or 'Tikhonova' (;
feminine) is a Russian last name and may refer to:

; People
* Andrey Nikolayevich Tikhonov, Russian mathematician
* Alexander Tikhonov, Russian biathlon athlete
* Alexei Tikhonov, Russian figure skater
* Andrey Valeryevich Tikhonov, Russian football player
* Konstantin Tikhonov, Soviet army officer and Hero of the Soviet Union
* Mikhail Tikhonov, Soviet soldier and Hero of the Soviet Union
* Nikita Tikhonov, suspect in Markelov murder case
* Nikolai Tikhonov, former Premier of the Soviet Union
* Nikolai Tikhonov (writer), Russian writer, a member of the Serapion Brothers
  literatury group
* Vasily Tikhonov (pilot), Soviet pilot and Hero of the Soviet Union
* Vasily Tikhonov, Soviet rower
* Vasily Ivanovich Tikhonov, Soviet soldier and Hero of the Soviet Union
* Viktor Pavlovich Tikhonov, Soviet pilot and Hero of the Soviet Union
* Viktor Vasilyevich Tikhonov, former coach for the Soviet national ice
  hockey team
* Vladimir Tikhonov, Russian politician
* Vyacheslav Tikhonov (1928-2009), Soviet actor

; Mathematics
* Tychonoff spaces, completely regular topological spaces
* Tychonoff's theorem, a result on topological spaces
* the Tychonoff separation axioms in topology
* Tikhonov distribution is a random variable distribution
* Tikhonov regularization, a method of regularization of ill-posed problems

; Other
* Tikhonov (rural locality), a rural locality (a khutor) in the Republic of
  Adygea, Russia
